						               													<description>A long time ago, Japan was banned from black tea due to the war with Britain.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;But people couldn't resist the charm of black tea.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Beautiful colors peeking out of the cup, unique scent, and noble and mellow taste...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rich people raised a lot of money in search of black tea, and some people tried to fulfill their wishes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;That was the moment when the mafia organization &amp;quot;Yokohama Syndicate&amp;quot; specializing in black tea was born in the port city of Yokohama.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;And time has passed and it is modern.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Black tea has not been lifted yet, mafias continue to carry it...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Times have changed, but things haven't changed, and people call them wearing maid clothes and paint guns, Maid Mafia!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Maid Mafia! is a game of smuggling. Each player moves around Yokohama city, gathers armed maids (fifteen in total) and traffics in black tea. A player who got three victory point cards first wins, but if the police act a certain number of times, all the players lose.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
